                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18370814-1809-offence-1 t18370814-name-349"></join>Henry Taylor</persName>, his master.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370814-name-350" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-350" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-350" type="surname" value="TAYLOR"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-350" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY TAYLOR</persName>
                  </hi>. I reside at Tottenham, and keep a beer-shop—the prisoner was pot-boy there. On Tuesday, the 18th of July, he came, and laid a lady at Mrs. Emery's wanted 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. in silver, and he gave me the sovereign—he came the same evening, and had change for another sovereign—I gave him two half-crowns, the rest in shillings and sixpences—he said it was for a lady at Mrs. Emery's, which proved to be Mrs. venables—the prisoner went away, and I saw no more of him till the next Saturday.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I said, "Master, I want a pound's worth of silver," and I laid it was for a lady—I did not say at Mrs. Emery's.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370814-name-351" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-351" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-351" type="surname" value="VENABLES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-351" type="given" value="ANNE MONK"></interp>ANNE MONK VENABLES</persName>
                  </hi>. I did not send the prisoner to Mr. Taylor's, desiring him to send 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. in silver for a sovereign, on the 18th of July.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> She did not at that time, but she has done so before—I did not say that time that she sent me for it—I was a little in liquor when I asked Mr. Taylor for it—I asked him for it—he gave it me—I did not say it was to give change to any one.</p>
